      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The slow memory leak in your ECU project is a classic case of a \"gathering dust\" issue, where small, seemingly insignificant allocations add up over time. Here's a systematic approach to help you track down the leak:\n\n1. **Instrument the allocation**: Use a memory profiling tool like Valgrind or AddressSanitizer to instrument the allocation of memory in your program. This will give you a detailed report of all memory allocations and deallocations, helping you identify the source of the leak.\n\n2. **Create a memory leak detector**: Write a custom function that periodically checks for memory leaks by iterating over all allocated memory blocks and checking if they are still valid. You can use a simple data structure like a linked list to keep track of all allocated memory blocks.\n\n3. **Analyze the telemetry handling class**: As you've already suspected, the telemetry handling class is a prime suspect. Look for any other classes or functions that allocate memory in a similar way. You can use the memory leak detector to identify any suspicious allocations.\n\n4. **Use a heap dump**: Periodically take a heap dump of your program's memory usage, which can help you identify the source of the leak. You can use tools like VisualVM or HeapWalk to",
